- used for memory management

1. variable
	- declared inside the class but outside the body of the method and
	declared with static keyword
	- shared among all objects
2. method
	- belongs to class rather than object of a class
	- without creating an object of class,static method can be invoked
	- static method can access static data member & can change the value of it
	- non static member can not be accessed in static methods
3. block
	- executes before main method at the time of class loading
	- till JDK 1.6 we can execute java class without main method.
	Since JDK 1.7, it is not possible to execute Java class without main method
	get error :  can't find main(String[]) method in class
4. class

